title: Seacoast Roundup: Murray nets two goals for St. Thomas girls
text: EPPING — Evelyn Carleton scored two goals as Epping (12-3) won this Division IV match. Meghan Galante assisted on Galante's first goal. Epping goalie Chloe Pelletier had two saves. Pingree 7 Berwick 1 SOUTH BERWICK, Maine — Laura Hoy scored for Berwick Academy (8-2-3) with assists from Christie Sullivan and Kenza Farid in this Eastern Independent League contest. Berwick goalie Sam Montagno played well. BOYS SOCCER Phillips Exeter 2 Berwick 0 SOUTH BERWICK, Maine — Brendan Tribastone and defender Jack McCraven played well for Berwick (7-1-4) in this loss. FIELD HOCKEY Berwick 4 LCA 0 SOUTH BERWICK, Maine — Olivia Varano had two goals, while Lily Reed and Sydney Hopkins each had one for Berwick Academy in this Eastern Independent League contest.
